On the 50th anniversary of Earth Day, President Donald Trump released a statement reaffirming the United States' commitment to environmental stewardship and conservation. The statement highlights the country's history of environmental leadership and mentions efforts to remove trash from oceans, clean up Superfund sites, revitalize communities through the Brownfields program, and join the Trillion Trees Initiative. The President also emphasizes the United States' achievements in clean air and access to clean drinking water, as well as the importance of preserving the nation's lands, air, waters, and wildlife while promoting responsible use of natural resources and expanding recreational opportunities. Melania and President Trump pledge to continue their efforts in ensuring that Americans can enjoy the natural beauty of the country for generations to come.